.TH FORMAT 3 "2026-07-17" "libctools" "libctools Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
println \- formatted output conversion and printing with implicit newline
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <libctools.h>
.HP
.BI "void println(const char *" format ", ...);"
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR println ()
function writes output to the standard output stream
.BR stdout .
It automatically appends a newline character to the output.
.PP
The
.I format
argument is a character string that contains formatting directives similar to those in
.BR printf (3).
.PP
This function is designed to be highly optimal and safe:
.IP \(bu 3
.B Thread Safety:
It internally wraps execution in
.BR flockfile (3)
and
.BR funlockfile (3)
to guarantee that concurrent logging from multiple threads does not interleave.
.IP \(bu 3
.B Fast-Path Rendering:
If the format string does not contain any format specifiers (no '%' characters), it bypasses the heavy
.BR vfprintf (3)
engine entirely and falls back to a fast raw write.
.IP \(bu 3
.B Security:
The function prototype enforces compile-time type-safety checks via GCC attributes to catch incorrect format string arguments.
.SH RETURN VALUE
None.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR flockfile (3)